==English==

===Etymology===
Middle English, from Latin ''congru&#275;ns'', present participle of ''congruere'', to meet together, agree.

===Adjective===
'''congruent'''
# [[Corresponding]] in [[character]].
# [[Harmonious]].
# ''(mathematics):'' Having a [[difference]] [[divisible]] by a [[modulus]].
# ''(mathematics):'' [[Coinciding]] [[exactly]] when [[superimposed]].

